\begin_layout Section
I: Launching Questions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Your launch implementation discussion should cover the following aspects,
 possibly for each phase of launch: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Target Market: 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Will you initially launch for just a particular city or a particular school?
 What is your initial target market? 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
User Types / Components: If there are multiple types of users (e.g., drivers
 and riders), we may launch to these users separately: at different times
 and in different ways.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
MVP or Full Product: Will you launch an early minimum-viable product (MVP),
 or will you wait until the product is fairly full featured? 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Distribution: What stores and sales channels will carry your product? What
 platforms will you launch on?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Rollout: When will it launch to different types of users? Are you going
 to start with a private beta? Will invitations be required? 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Buzz: How will you build buzz around your product (or will you)? Who will
 you reach out to? How will you get them on board? What do you want them
 to say about your product? 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Partnerships: Are there any partnerships that will help you to achieve your
 vision?
\end_layout

