\begin_layout Section
Design Email
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A little design exercise we’ve developed over time is to assume someone
 will only read a subject line, the first headline in the email, and the
 call-to-action (the biggest visual anchors).
 If everything else was removed, would it still make sense? That’s the north
 star we aim for when designing an effective email.
\end_layout

